<hl>
<seg id=1> Opportunities Five-fold for Hong Kong In Economic Development Of Inland China: Gu Yongjiang </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Gu Yongjiang spoke of the following five opportunities for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region that the economic development of the interior will present: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> It will assist in stabilizing long-term prosperity for Hong Kong's economy. </seg>
<seg id=4> The interior is experiencing stable long-term economic growth, so Hong Kong's economy will benefit from the interior's vigorous economy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> It can offer Hong Kong even more commercial opportunities. </seg>
<seg id=6> As the region's trade, financial and retail services become more open to the outside world, Hong Kong's service industry will find wider room to develop there. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> It will help to solidify Hong Kong as a center of trade and shipping. </seg>
<seg id=8> In 2010 the interior's trade with the outside world is expected to reach 800 billion U.S. dollars, undoubtedly increasing its need for Hong Kong as a transfer point for trade and shipping. This will help to consolidate Hong Kong's position as a center of trade and shipping. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> It will promote the development of Hong Kong's financial market. </seg>
<seg id=10> As China's economic reforms deepen, there will be even more joint-stock companies entering markets outside of the country; among markets beyond the interior's borders, Hong Kong will be the first choice. </seg>
<seg id=11> This will enlarge the scale of Hong Kong's stock market, improve its organization, and push the development of the city's securities market. Even more Chinese money will make an appearance in Hong Kong.  As a result, Hong Kong's position as an international financial center will be solidified and strengthened. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> It will strengthen the international competitiveness of products from Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=13> A superior position will be reached through the economic relationship that the interior and Hong Kong share, which will be able to strengthen the international competitiveness of products from Hong Kong. </seg>
</p>
